      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Seven states",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://giffords.org/lawcenter/gun-laws/policy-areas/hardware-ammunition/assault-weapons/#:~:text=Seven%20states%20and%20the%20District,of%20Columbia%20prohibit%20assault%20weapons.",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " — Hawai’i, California, New York, Massachusetts, Maryland, New Jersey, and Connecticut — ban assault weapons, in addition to the District of Columbia. Studies have found that the federal assault weapons ban in place from 1994 to 2004 was successful in reducing ",
